# note1

  If $f \left( x, y \right) + f \left( y, z \right) = g \left( x, z \right)$
  for $\forall x, y, z$, then $\exists h, s.t.f \left( x, y \right) = h \left(
  x \right) - h \left( y \right) + C$ where $C$ is a constant

**Proof**:

  We have $f \left( x, x \right) + f \left( x, x \right) = g \left( x, x
  \right) \Longrightarrow f \left( x, x \right) = \frac{g \left( x, x
  \right)}{2}$
  
  $f \left( x, y \right) + f \left( y, x \right) = g \left( x, x \right), f
  \left( y, x \right) + f \left( x, y \right) = g \left( y, y \right)
  \Longrightarrow g \left( x, x \right) = g \left( y, y \right), \forall x, y$
  
  $f \left( x, x \right) + f \left( x, y \right) = g \left( x, y \right)$
  
  Let $g \left( x, x \right) = 2 C, f \left( x, x \right) = C$, we have $f
  \left( x, y \right) = g \left( x, y \right) - f \left( x, x \right) = f
  \left( x, 0 \right) + f \left( 0, y \right) - f \left( x, x \right) = f
  \left( x, 0 \right) + g \left( 0, 0 \right) - f \left( y, 0 \right) - f
  \left( x, x \right) = f \left( x, 0 \right) - f \left( y, 0 \right) + C$.
  Let $h \left( x \right) = f \left( x, 0 \right)$ the proof is completed.1
